# 2026-02-25 10:09:47.817561
+You are fixing the MQTT WebSocket connection in src/app/test-connections/page.tsx.
+
+Current problem:
+- Browser console shows repeated error: WebSocket connection to 'ws://localhost:9001/mqtt' failed: The network connection was lost.
+- MQTT card stays "Disconnected" / "MQTT client offline"
+- Supabase is already green – do not touch it.
+
+Fix requirements – do all of these exactly:
+
+1. Use this exact URL: ws://localhost:9001/mqtt
+   - Read from process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_MQTT_BROKER_URL
+   - Fallback: 'ws://localhost:9001/mqtt'
+   - Log immediately: console.log('Attempting MQTT WS connect to:', mqttUrl)
+
+2. mqtt.connect options must include:
+   - protocol: 'ws'
+   - reconnectPeriod: 3000
+   - connectTimeout: 10000
+   - rejectUnauthorized: false   // for local dev
+   - clientId: 'waterfront-browser-' + Math.random().toString(16).slice(3)
+
+3. Add detailed event handlers:
+   - on('connect'): 
+     console.log('MQTT CONNECTED to ' + mqttUrl)
+     setStatus({ status: 'connected', message: 'Connected to broker' })
+   - on('error'): 
+     console.error('MQTT ERROR:', err)
+     setStatus({ status: 'error', message: 'Connection error: ' + (err.message || err) })
+   - on('offline'): 
+     console.log('MQTT OFFLINE')
+     setStatus({ status: 'disconnected', message: 'Offline – reconnecting...' })
+   - on('close'): 
+     console.log('MQTT CLOSED')
+   - on('reconnect'): 
+     console.log('MQTT reconnect attempt')
+
+4. Cleanup: return () => client.end() in useEffect
+
+5. "Send Test Message" button:
+   - Disabled if status !== 'connected'
+   - On click: 
+     const payload = JSON.stringify({
+       action: "test_unlock",
+       kayakId: "test-001",
+       timestamp: new Date().toISOString()
+     })
+     client.publish('/kayak/test/unlock', payload, { qos: 1 }, (err) => {
+       if (err) console.error('Publish failed:', err)
+       else console.log('Test message published successfully')
+     })
+
+6. Keep loading state, refresh button, and all existing UI/Tailwind.
+
+Do NOT remove console.log lines – they are for debugging.
+
+After changes:
+- Remind user to:
+  1. Confirm docker logs mqtt-broker shows "Opening websocket listener on port 9001"
+  2. Run pnpm dev
